commitResults.messageBody: Completion of Add Increment: Level-0 of individual project.
Added indentation for "Bye. Hope to see you again soon!" and improved coding standards

commitResults.messageTitle: Add Increment: Level-1: Greet, Echo, Exit
commitResults.messageBody: This is a skeletal version of Duke that starts by greeting the user, simply echoes commands entered by the user, and exits when the user types "bye".

This version of Duke has the ability to store whatever text entered by the user and display them back to the user when requested. Since arrayList is used, the limit on the number of the user inputs depends on the computer memory.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add Increment: Level-3: Mark as Done
commitResults.messageBody:
This version of Duke has the ability to mark tasks as done. It also
alerts the user that the list is empty and prompts him or her to enter
again in the event that the user types "list" at the start of the
program (when there is no task to do).
This version of Duke tweaks the code to comply with CS2113T coding standard.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add Increment: Level-4: ToDos, Events, Deadlines
commitResults.messageBody:
This version of Duke adds support for tracking three types of tasks:
ToDos, Deadlines and Events.

This version of Duke deals with errors such as incorrect inputs entered
by the user.
